<h1 class="Article-title">Toggle</h1>
<p class="Text--lead">Hide, switch or change the appearance of different contents through a toggle.</p>

<hr class="Article-divider">

<h2 id="section-usage"><a href="#section-usage" class="Text--resetLink">Usage</a></h2>

<p>The toggle module is loaded asynchronously and is initialised using <code>data-module="Toggle"</code> on the toggler element.</p>
<p>By default the module toggles the default active class (<code>is-active</code>) on itself.</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button" data-module="Toggle">Click me to toggle me</button>
  <button class="Button is-active" data-module="Toggle">Click me to toggle me</button>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot;&gt;Click to toggle me&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h3 id="section-options"><a href="#section-options" class="Text--resetLink">Options</a></h3>

<h4>Once</h4>
<p>You can set the toggle module to only toggle once (<code>data-options='{"once":true}'</code>).</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"once":true}'>You can only turn me on</button>
  <button class="Button is-active" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"once":true}'>You can only turn me off</button>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;once&quot;:true}&#39;&gt;You can only turn me on&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h4>Target</h4>
<p>You can also toggle an active class on another element using the target option (<code>data-options='{"target":"#mydiv"}'</code>).</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button myButton" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"target":"#mydiv"}'>Click me to toggle the div</button>
  <div class="Demo Demo--fat" id="mydiv"></div>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button myButton&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;#mydiv&quot;}&#39;&gt;
    Click to toggle the div
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<p>You can also pass in the string 'parent' to specifically target source element's direct parent element.</p>
<div class="docs-example">
  <div class="Demo Demo--fat">
    <button class="Button myButton" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"target":"parent"}'>Click me to toggle the div</button>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv&quot;&gt;
  &lt;button class=&quot;Button myButton&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;parent&quot;}&#39;&gt;
    Click to toggle the div
  &lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<p>You can also multiple element by passing in an array (<code>data-options='{"target":["#mydiv1","#mydiv2"]}'</code>).</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button myButton" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"target":["#mydiv1","#mydiv2"]}'>Click to toggle the both divs</button>
  <div class="o-Grid o-Grid--gutters">
    <div class="o-Grid-cell">
      <div class="Demo Demo--fat" id="mydiv1"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="o-Grid-cell">
      <div class="Demo Demo--fat" id="mydiv2"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button myButton&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;target&quot;:[&quot;#mydiv1&quot;,&quot;#mydiv2&quot;]}&#39;&gt;
    Click to toggle both divs
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv1&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv2&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h4>Active class</h4>
<p>You can also toggle an custom active class using the 'activeClass' option (<code>data-options='{"activeClass":"is-alt-active"}'</code>).</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button myButton" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"target":"#mydiv3","activeClass":"is-alt-active"}'>Click to toggle the div</button>
  <div class="Demo Demo--fat" id="mydiv3"></div>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button myButton&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;activeClass&quot;:&quot;is-alt-active&quot;,&quot;target&quot;:&quot;#mydiv3&quot;}&#39;&gt;
    Click to toggle the div
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv3&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

<h4>Hide</h4>
<p>Instead of toggling an active class, you can toggle an elements display property by using the 'hide' option (<code>data-options='{"hide":true}</code>). This toggles the 'hidden' attribute on the target(s).</p>
<p><strong class="Badge">Note</strong> If you use this option, the active class is no longer toggled.</p>

<div class="docs-example">
  <button class="Button myButton" data-module="Toggle" data-options='{"target":"#mydiv4", "hide":true}'>Click to hide/show the div</button>
  <div class="Demo Demo--fat" id="mydiv4"></div>
</div>
<div class="docs-code docs-code--html">
  <pre><code class="html">&lt;button class=&quot;Button myButton&quot; data-module=&quot;Toggle&quot; data-options=&#39;{&quot;target&quot;:&quot;#mydiv&quot;}&#39;&gt;
    Click to hide/show the div
&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;mydiv&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
</div>

